content.description: Climb the obvious beautiful thick flake. The crux is right off the ground, working right through the 4" placement and up and right over the overlap. After that the rest of the route is at most 5.8+, as the higher right-trending crack hasÂ plenty of great feet.
content.protection: 1 4" cam for the low crux, 2 3" cams higher up are helpful. Otherwise a few varied 0.5-2" cams. Anchor updated to stainless half inchers 10/25/2017.
content.location: The obvious crack splitting a clean face on the island across from Roadside Rock aka Highway rock.

content.description: A tricky face start (crux) to a thin smooth quartz-lined tips crack to the left of Prime Cut. Allegedly goes at 11a. The route is currently dirty and in need of gardening. It probably hasn't been climbed more than a few times, but would be a worthy clean-up project.
content.protection: Unknown. Shares anchor with Prime Cut, can probably be top roped from that anchor.
content.location: To the left of Prime Cut.
